<p><b>Other types of Schedulers</b></p>

<p>You can use the Scheduler editing form to create
 custom schedulers. Examples below.</p>

<p><b>Example 1</b>: This schedule pulls 100%
 of the non-test exercises from each topic 
	added to the newest homework, but automatically
	 applies two different labels.</p>
	<p>
	<center><%= image_tag("schedule3.png", {:border => 1, :width => "95%", 
   :title=>"schedule"})%></center></p>
<p><strong>Example 2</strong>: This schedule will 
	yield assignments that include exercises from both 
  (i) the current topic and (ii) topics covered 
  <em>two assignments ago</em> (a form of 
  <%= link_to_help 'spaced_practice', 
  text="spaced practice", {:title => 'Spaced Practice', 
  	:width => '600', :height => '500'} %>).</p>
<p>
<p><center><%= image_tag("schedule1.png", {:border => 1, :width => "95%", 
   :title=>"schedule"})%></center></p> 
<p>  
<p><strong>Example 3</strong>: You can also create
 <em><strong>multiple schedules</strong></em>. Given 
  multiple schedules, OST will cycle through the schedules in order. </p> 
